ager and the board is confident that captain blackley will continue to execute on the companys strategic vision provide the highest quality service to our customers and deliver value for our shareholders doug wheat further commented that the board searched and interviewed extensively for the ceo position and after consideration of the attributes necessary to lead the company determined that captain blackley had the best overall experience and knowledge of the shipping business and osg to lead the company i am honored and privileged to serve as president and ceo of osg at this time in our history and i am excited to build upon the companys new momentum and success captain blackley said i look forward to our next phase of growth as a leading company in the maritime industry and to our full return to the capital markets as a publicly traded company in august  osg announced its search for a new chief executive officer to lead the companys growth efforts after emergence from its chapter  reorganization henry flinter head of the us flag business and lois zabrocky head of the international flag business will continue as heads of their respective business units and will report directly to captain blackley prior to his roles of chief operating officer and chief financial officer captain blackley was senior vice president and head of international shipping operations responsible for the operational management of osgs international flag fleet as well as oversight of technical management and training operations captain blackley was also managing director and chief operating officer of osg ship management uk ltd if you liked this article you might like  stocks going exdividend tomorrow osgb nsh simo osgb nsh simo are going exdividend tomorrow thursday may   thestreet wire may    am edt  sellrated dividend stocks osgb mitt bkep these  dividend stocks are rated a sell by thestreet thestreet wire apr    am edt  sellrated dividend stocks osgb trox ladr these  dividend stocks are rat